All Classes

  • All Classes Class Summary Enum Summary 
    Class Description
    AnalysisService
    Provides access to summary statistics about a MYA channel data.
    DataNexus
    Manages the possibly multiple data sources required to service requests to a cluster of Mya hosts, which make up a deployment.
    DataType
    Mya DataTypes.
    Event
    A Mya history event such as an update or discontinuity marker.
    EventCode
    Mya event codes.
    EventStream<T extends Event>
    Provides an I/O Channel for streaming Mya events.
    ExtraInfo
    Provides additional information about an EPICS PV, which unlike standard Metadata, is versioned (may change over time).
    FloatEvent
    Represents a Mya history event for a PV of data type float.
    FloatEventBucket
    This is intended to be used as the "bucket" in a modified implementation of the largest triangle three bucket (LTTB) algorithm described in "Downsampling Time Series for Visual Representation" (Steinarsson, 2013).
    FloatEventStream
    EventStream of FloatEvents.
    FloatGraphicalEventBinSampleStream
    Wraps a FloatEventStream and provides FloatEvents that are down-sampled as they stream by using an algorithm which attempts to maintain graphical fidelity of the data.
    FloatIntegrationStream
    Wraps a FloatEventStream and provides FloatEvents by that are integrated as they stream by.
    FloatSimpleEventBinSampleStream
    Wraps a FloatEventStream and provides FloatEvents that are down-sampled as they stream by using a simple algorithm.
    GraphicalEventBinSamplerParams
    Parameters for the advanced sampler; uses the largest triangle three bucket (LTTB) algorithm described in "Downsampling Time Series for Visual Representation" (Steinarsson, 2013).
    IntervalQueryParams
    The parameters required to query for events in an interval with an inclusive begin timestamp and exclusive end timestamp.
    IntervalService
    Provides query access to the Mya database for a set of events in a given time interval.
    IntEvent
    Represents a Mya history event for a PV of data type int.
    IntEventStream
    EventStream of IntEvents.
    LabeledEnumEvent
    Represents a Mya history event for a PV of data type enum, which has been assigned a label.
    LabeledEnumStream
    Wraps an IntEventStream and provides LabelEnumEvents by assigning enumeration labels to integer values.
    Metadata
    The metadata associated with an EPICS PV.
    MultiStringEvent
    Represents a Mya history event for a PV that is vector in nature (regardless of data type) or a PV that is not a scalar int or float.
    MultiStringEventStream
    EventStream of MultiStringEvents.
    MyGetSampleParams
    Parameters for the myget sampler algorithm (myget -l).
    MySamplerFloatEventStream
    EventStream for the MySampler algorithm.
    MySamplerParams
    Parameters for the MYA mySampler algorithm (mySampler).
    OnDemandNexus
    A Mya DataNexus which creates resources on-demand and closes them immediately after use.
    PointQueryParams
    The parameters required to query for a single event near a point in time.
    PointService
    Provides query access to the Mya database for a single event near a point in time.
    PooledNexus
    A Mya DataNexus which pools resources for later use.
    QueryParams
    The parameters required to query for events.
    QueryService
    Provides query access to the Mya database.
    RunningStatistics
    This class provides summary statistics about the specified set of MYA data.
    SimpleEventBinSamplerParams
    Parameters for the simple event bin sampler; performs application layer filtering.
    SourceSamplingService
    Provides query access to the Mya database for a set of source (in-database) sampled events in a given time interval.
    TimeUtil
    Utility methods for conversion between Mya's database time format and Java's native Instant.
    WrappedEventStreamAdaptor<T extends Event,​E extends Event>
    Adaptor for classes wishing to wrap an EventStream.
